The paper deals with the problem of downlink channel state information (CSI) prediction for frequency division duplexing (FDD) massive multiple-input multiple-output (MIMO) systems using artificial intelligence (AI) techniques. This involves developing a deep transfer learning (DTL) algorithm that can adapt to new environments with limited labeled data. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE), Systems and Control (cs.SY), and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories.
